      "antimicrobialStewardship": [
        "The development of gonococcal resistance has been inexorable. Multiple drug resistance is increasing, with reports of strains resistant to both ceftriaxone and azithromycin.",
        "National and international guidelines have been formulated to slow the selection and spread of resistant organisms.",
        "Double coverage had been recommended since 1985, but due to the effects of macrolides on the microbiome and resistance emergence, azithromycin is no longer recommended with Ceftriaxone in the US as of the 2020 recommendations."
      ],
      "drugSpecificPearls": [
        {
          "drugName": "Azithromycin",
          "pearl": "A 2g dose is associated with frequent GI side effects, high cost, and concerns about increasing resistance."
        },
        {
          "drugName": "Spectinomycin",
          "pearl": "Available outside the U.S. but is not efficacious for pharyngeal infections."
        }
      ],
